body:
I observed duplication of nodes thus AST blow up during V3DfgPeephole phase, in `PUSH_SEL_THROUGH_COND` pass. I suspect it is caused by double-visits of `CONCAT` nodes, but work list seems to be working fine.
I'm attaching tree dumps for `good` run (with `--fno-dfg-peephole-push-sel-through-cond`) and `bad` run.

[good.tree.txt](https://github.com/user-attachments/files/20624096/good.tree.txt)
[bad.tree.txt](https://github.com/user-attachments/files/20624097/bad.tree.txt)

@gezalore Do you have any insight on possible causes of this behavior?

```python
#!/usr/bin/env python3
# DESCRIPTION: Verilator: Verilog Test driver/expect definition
#
# Copyright 2025 by Wilson Snyder. This program is free software; you
# can redistribute it and/or modify it under the terms of either the GNU
